title = 'my-angular-app6';
}
14. How Routing Works
User Enters URL
│
▼
Angular Checks Routes
│
├───────────────► Route Found
│ │
│ ▼
│ Open Matching Component
│
└───────────────► No Route Found
│
▼
Wildcard Route (**)
│
▼
Display Not Found Page15. Summary
In this article, we learned:

• How to redirect one route to another using redirectTo

• Why pathMatch: 'full' is required

• How the wildcard route ('**') catches invalid URLs

• How to create a simple 404 Page Not Found component
